# Wallets – List Wallet Transactions
# Smoke tests for GET /users/me/wallet/transactions.
#
# Authenticated-user endpoint. Returns a paginated list of the requesting
# user's wallet transactions (cashback credits and reversals), ordered newest
# first. Query parameters: limit (1–100, default 10) and offset (≥0, default 0).
# The user identity is derived from the JWT, so no user_id is in the path.
#
# Seed data (seeds/all.sql):
#   alice (b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d)
#     7 transactions (5 pending credits, 1 available credit, 1 pending from rejection-sim)
#   bob (c8d3e2b1-5a4b-4c3d-8b2a-7e6f5d4c3b2a)
#     6 transactions (3 pending credits, 1 available credit, 1 reversal, 1 pending from rejection-sim)
#   carol (d9f4b3c2-6b5c-5d4e-7c3b-6a5e4d3c2b1a)
#     2 transactions (1 pending credit, 1 reversal)
#   jero (d9f4b3c2-6b5c-5d4e-7c3b-6a5e4d3c2b1b)
#     0 transactions (no cashback activity)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8001/api/v1

# Expired local-dev placeholder — never a real credential.
# Run the login helper below and paste the returned access_token to refresh.
@aliceToken = Bearer insert_token_here
@bobToken   = Bearer insert_token_here
@jeroToken  = Bearer insert_token_here

### Helper – obtain a fresh alice token
# Returns access_token — paste as "Bearer <token>" into @aliceToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

###

### Helper – obtain a fresh bob token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

###

### 200 – Happy path: alice's transactions (default pagination)
# Expects: 7 transactions total, all types present (cashback_credit / pending+available,
# and whatever the rejection-sim purchase yields).
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 200 – Happy path: bob's transactions — includes a reversed cashback
# Expects: transactions including one with type=reversal, status=reversed.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions
Authorization: {{bobToken}}

###

### 200 – Happy path: jero's transactions — no cashback activity
# Expects: { "transactions": [], "total": 0 }
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions
Authorization: {{jeroToken}}

###

### 200 – Pagination: alice's transactions, first page of 3
# Expects: 3 items returned (the 3 most recent), total reflects full count (7).
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?limit=3&offset=0
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 200 – Pagination: alice's transactions, second page of 3
# Expects: next 3 items, skipping the first 3.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?limit=3&offset=3
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 200 – Pagination: beyond the last page
# Expects: empty transactions array, total still reflects full count.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?limit=10&offset=100
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 422 – Sad path: invalid limit (below minimum)
# Expects: 422 Unprocessable Entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?limit=0
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 422 – Sad path: invalid limit (above maximum)
# Expects: 422 Unprocessable Entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?limit=101
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 422 – Sad path: invalid offset (negative)
# Expects: 422 Unprocessable Entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions?offset=-1
Authorization: {{aliceToken}}

###

### 401 – Sad path: unauthenticated request (no Authorization header)
# Expects: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions
